{"questionId":"32049836","questionHtml":"<p>the maximum value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>F</mi></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>substituting <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math> into formula for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></math> &nbsp; <strong>OR&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math> into <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>y</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: <em><strong>M1</strong></em> may be awarded for an appropriate table with at least one correct value for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>F</mi></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi></math>, even if there is no evidence of substitution into the Euler equations.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>F</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>000004</mn><msub><mi>F</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><msub><mi>L</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>F</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo></math> &nbsp; AND &nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>L</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>L</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>06</mn><msub><mi>L</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>-</mo><mn>0</m